In [ ]:
t_test_results = {}

label_encoders = {}

# Perform a t-test for each demographic variable
for i, col in enumerate(dem_columns):
    le = LabelEncoder()
    df[f'{col}_num'] = le.fit_transform(df[col].astype(str))
    
    label_encoders[col] = le

    group_A = df[df['group'] == 'A'][f'{col}_num']
    group_B = df[df['group'] == 'B'][f'{col}_num']

    t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group_A, group_B, equal_var=False, nan_policy='omit')
    
    t_test_results[col] = {'t-statistic': t_stat, 'p-value': p_value}

fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(20, 10))

# Plot the distribution of each demographic variable
for i, column in enumerate(dem_columns):
    group_A_distribution = df[df['group'] == 'A'][column].value_counts(normalize=True)
    group_B_distribution = df[df['group'] == 'B'][column].value_counts(normalize=True)
    
    distribution_df = pd.DataFrame({'Group A': group_A_distribution, 'Group B': group_B_distribution}).fillna(0)
    
    # Bar plot
    distribution_df.sort_values(by='Group A').plot(kind='barh', ax=axs[i], color=['#9B6EF8', '#12CAD6'])
    
    axs[i].set_title(title_dict[column], fontsize=15)
    axs[i].set_xlabel('Proportion of respondents')
    axs[i].legend()

Environmental involvement analysis¶

In [ ]:
# Define the orderings for the Likert scale responses
ordering_inv_1_3 = ['Never', 'Sometimes', 'Quite often', 'Most of the time', 'Always']
ordering_inv_2 = ['Strongly disagree', 'Somewhat disagree', 'Neither agree nor disagree', 'Somewhat agree', 'Strongly agree']

title_dict = {
    'inv_1': 'Q1: How often do you feel worried about climate change?',
    'inv_2': 'Q2: To what degree do you agree with the viewpoint that human actions are the primary cause of climate change?',
    'inv_3': 'Q3: How often do you consider environmental sustainability while purchasing a product?',
    'involvement_score': 'Calculated environmental involvement score (sum of Q1, Q2, Q3 5-point Likert responses)'
}

inv_columns = [column for column in df.columns if column.startswith('inv_') and '_num' not in column and column != 'involvement_score']
inv_columns.append('involvement_score')

fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(20, 10),)

axs = axs.flatten()

# Plot the distribution of each "inv_" variable
for i, column in enumerate(inv_columns):
    distribution = df[column].value_counts().sort_index()

    # Reorder the index based on the defined orderings
    if column in ['inv_1', 'inv_3']:
        distribution = distribution.reindex(ordering_inv_1_3)
    elif column == 'inv_2':
        distribution = distribution.reindex(ordering_inv_2)
    
    # Bar plot
    distribution.plot(kind='barh', ax=axs[i], color='#F94B48')
    
    axs[i].set_title(title_dict[column], fontsize=13)
    axs[i].set_xlabel('Number of respondents')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

print("STATISTICAL INSIGHTS")

print('Std of involvement score:', np.std(df['involvement_score']))

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

means = {
    'Scenario 1': {
        'Positive': np.mean(df['s1_pos_num']),
        'Negative': np.mean(df['s1_neg_num']),
    },
    'Scenario 2': {
        'Positive': np.mean(df['s2_pos_num']),
        'Negative': np.mean(df['s2_neg_num']),
    }
}

df_means = pd.DataFrame(means)

df_means_transposed = df_means.transpose()

colors = {'Negative': '#f94b48', 'Positive': '#9b6ef8'}

neg = negnan[~np.isnan(negnan)]

# Split the dataframe based on the "group" column
df_group_A = df[df['group'] == 'A']
df_group_B = df[df['group'] == 'B']

model1 = smf.ols(formula='s1_pos_num ~ involvement_score',
                data=df_group_A).fit()
model2 = smf.ols(formula='s2_neg_num ~ involvement_score',
                data=df_group_A).fit()
model3 = smf.ols(formula='s1_neg_num ~ involvement_score',
                data=df_group_B).fit()
model4 = smf.ols(formula='s2_pos_num ~ involvement_score',
                data=df_group_B).fit()
  
# model summary
stargazer = Stargazer([model1, model2, model3, model4])
prerender = stargazer.render_html()

# Make substitutions
prerender = prerender.replace("(1)", "(S1_pos)")
prerender = prerender.replace("(2)", "(S2_neg)")
prerender = prerender.replace("(3)", "(S1_neg)")
prerender = prerender.replace("(4)", "(S2_pos)")

def export_to_png(html_content, output_file):
    imgkit.from_string(html_content, output_file, options={'format': 'png', 'quiet': '', 'minimum-font-size':18}, config=imgkit.config(wkhtmltoimage='/usr/local/bin/wkhtmltoimage'))

def bar():
    chart = HTML(prerender)
    display(chart)
    export_to_png(prerender, "images/regressions.png")
